Top positive reviewSee all 10 positive reviews› 
          One person found this helpful
5.0 out of 5 starsI really enjoyed the world of magic presented by the authorByAmazon Customeron June 8, 2016I really enjoyed the world of magic presented by the author.. The main character's refusal to use magic violently or to hurt others and the consternation which this causes among the other characters creates good and believable tension. A thoughtful look at the pros and cons of violence and how our culture influences our view of reality and good and bad. This new world with its many characters is Harry Potteresque. I can't wait for the next volume.

Read more
Top critical reviewSee all 2 critical reviews› 
          One person found this helpful
3.0 out of 5 starsThis is a great first bookByMelon January 23, 2016This is a great first book; I liked it. I WANT more people to read it! Why? Because I know the author will improve in his future novels and go on to become a great and talented novelist. This is just the beginning for him, so I will read the sequel and whatever other books that he produces because he shows promise. The author was masterfully creative in coming up with new species and cultures. I am a fantasy junkie and hadn't heard of some of the races he used so, kudos my good man! Great storyline too; It was classic.  I did not enjoy the redundancy of many scenes and/or dialogue that had to be repeated. The book is an alternating third person perspective and so I understand much of the overlap; I just did not like it. The main characters were strong and I enjoyed their conflict and developement. That being said, I sometimes felt that their reactions to things were forced by the author in order to make more conflict. I also felt that the flow of information was inconsistent.

Read more





