						Appliance Delivery & Installation
			

 



Appliance Delivery & Installation





















		
	
		Free standard delivery on special orderappliance purchases $396 or more
		
	
		





































			Free Standard Delivery on Special Order Appliance purchases of $396 or more. Qualifying purchases include: Refrigeration, Laundry, Dishwashers, Cooking appliances and HDPP in addition to Installation and Parts/Accessories that accompany Depot Direct purchases. Floorcare and clearance appliances not included. A $59 delivery fee applies to any major appliance purchases below $396. Haul away of old appliances at additional charge. Offer valid only at participating stores in U.S., Guam and Puerto Rico The Home Depot® stores and on select major appliance purchases on www.homedepot.com. Delivery fees vary by zip code. See Store Associate for further details.Before a customer accepts delivery, major appliance products (including refrigerators, washers, dryers, ranges, dishwashers, and some microwaves) should be inspected for defects or damage, and if any exists, customer should refuse delivery. Once delivery is accepted by a customer, product may be returned if defects and/or damage is identified and reported to The Home Depot within 48 hours of delivery day by calling (800) 455-3869.













  			Delivery and Basic Hook up Service
  		





			Most freestanding electric refrigerators, ranges, washers & dryers are eligible for delivery & basic hook up service.Basic hook up service does not include hook up or removal of built in cooktops, wall ovens, drop ins and air conditioners. Commercial or built-in refrigeration (i.e. refrigerators with the compressor on top or over-sized units) cannot be installed/removed/hauled away. The installation must comply with local codes, or in the absence of local codes, with the National Fuel Gas Code and the National Electric Code.
		
	













		
			Refrigerators Video
	



Requirements and Preparation




					Water connection kit required


					110V-grounded, 3-prong electrical outlet
				
			

					Water valve (shutoff) within 6 ft. of hook up




		
	
		Prepare for Your Delivery




Measure the delivery path and new appliance area to make sure that your refrigerator will fit perfectly


Verify your existing electrical and water connections


					Empty & unplug your old refrigerator


Download the refrigerators checklistDownload the checklist in Spanish/Descarga la lista en Español















		
			Electric Ranges Video
	



Requirements and Preparation




					A new electrical cord
				
			

					A 240V electric outlet within 4 ft. of hookup




		
	
		Prepare for Your Delivery




					Verify that your outlet type matches the approved types shown above
				
			

					Empty & unplug your old appliance


Download the electric ranges checklistDownload the checklist in Spanish/Descarga la lista en Español















		
			Electric Dryers Video
	



Requirements and Preparation




					A new electrical cord and dryer duct 
				
			

					A 240V electric outlet within 4 ft. of hookup




Prepare for Your Delivery




					Verify that your outlet type matches the approved types shown above
				
			

					Empty & unplug your old appliance


Download the electric dryers checklistDownload the checklist in Spanish/Descarga la lista en Español















		
			Washing Machines Video
	



Requirements and Preparation




					New hoses (available at checkout)
				
			

					110V-grounded, 3-prong electrical outlet
				
			

					Water valves (hot and cold) must be corrosive free and within 6 ft. of hookup




Prepare for Your Delivery




Verify your existing electrical and water connections


					Empty & unplug your old appliance


Download the washing machines checklistDownload the checklist in Spanish/Descarga la lista en Español














  			Delivery and Additional Hook up Service
  		





			Additional hook up service applies to gas ranges & dryers, dishwashers, and over the range microwaves.  Hook up services are available for these items in some areas for an additional fee. The Home Depot cannot install gas dryers in a garage.For any questions, please contact our Appliance Support Hotline at 1-877-WIN-WTHD.
		
	













		
			Dishwashers Video
	



Requirements and Preparation




					New dishwasher connection kit
				
			

					Water supply line (shutoff) within 6 ft. of hook up
				
			

					Electrical outlet within 6 ft. of hook up
				
			

					The rough cabinet opening must be at least: 24" W X  24" D X 34–1/2" H




Prepare for Your Delivery




					Measure your rough cabinet opening
				
			

Verify your existing electrical and water connections


					Empty and unplug your old dishwasher


Download the dishwashers checklistDownload the checklist in Spanish/Descarga la lista en Español















		
			Gas Ranges Video
	



Requirements and Preparation




					New gas flex connection kit and dryer duct
				
			

					Natural gas line (no liquid propane hookups)
				
			

					110V-grounded, 3-prong electrical outlet
				
			

					Gas shutoff directly behind the appliance




Prepare for Your Delivery




Verify your existing electrical & water connections


					Empty & unplug your old appliance


Download the gas ranges checklistDownload the checklist in Spanish/Descarga la lista en Español















		
			Gas Dryers Video
	



Requirements and Preparation




					New gas flex connection kit and dryer duct
				
			

					Natural gas line (no liquid propane hookups)
				
			

					110V-grounded, 3-prong electrical outlet
				
			

					Gas shutoff directly behind the appliance




Prepare for Your Delivery




Verify your existing electrical & water connections


					Empty & unplug your old appliance


Download the gas dryers checklistDownload the checklist in Spanish/Descarga la lista en Español















		
			Over the Range Microwaves Video
	



Requirements and Preparation




					Hardwiring will not be done. A dedicated 110V electric outlet must be directly above the unit




Prepare for Your Delivery




Download the over the range microwave checklistDownload the checklist in Spanish/Descarga la lista en Español














  			Additional Information
  		









		
	
		The Home Depot Advantage
		
	
		



When you choose The Home Depot for your Appliance Delivery & Installation, enjoy these benefits:




					Delivered electric appliances will be uncrated, set in place, leveled, and connected to an existing power source.
				
			

					Your installed appliance will be tested to make sure it works correctly.
				
			

					All packing materials will be removed and your home will be restored to its original condition.
				
			

					Additional hookup services for gas appliances, dishwashers and over the range microwaves available in some areas.









		
	
		Delivery Day
	




					The delivery company will contact you at least a day in advance of your scheduled delivery date to confirm the delivery and give you a time frame.
				
			

					You will receive a 30-minute call ahead on the day of delivery to let you know it's on the way.
				
			

					Someone over the age of 18 must be home to accept delivery of your new appliance.
				
			

					All delivery agents are required to display their authorized badge during delivery.
				
			



If you have any questions or concerns about your delivery, please call your Appliance Support Line at 1-877-WIN-WTHD.









		
	
		Protection Plans
		
	
			



Save more and worry less with The Home Depot Protection Plan on major appliances. Plans available both online (after adding appliances to your cart) and in-store.




Learn More














  			Frequently Asked Questions
  		













					I live in a 5 story walk up apartment, can I have my appliances delivered and installed?
			








			There must be less than 3 flights of stairs to get to install location (not applicable if elevator is available) with an available unloading zone within 30 ft of the home for parking & access.
		
	







					Will the delivery agents install using liquid propane hookups?
			








			The delivery agents are not licensed plumbers and will not install liquid propane.
		
	







					Will the delivery agent install a unitized (all-in-one) washer dryer?
			








			Installation is available in certain areas. Please contact our Appliance Support Hotline at 1-877-WIN-WTHD with questions.
		
	







					I want to have my frontload washer and dryer stacked to save space. Will the delivery agent install them that way?
			








			Appliance stacking is available in some areas, but is not included in the basic delivery rate. Please contact our Appliance Support Hotline at 1-877-WIN-WTHD with questions.
		
	







					What if my new appliance is damaged or not working correctly at the time of delivery?
			








			Make sure to examine and test your appliances before the delivery agent leaves. If you notice any damage or your appliance is not working correctly, raise any issues at the time of delivery with your delivery agent.
		
	
















  			Easy Home Delivery and Installation
  		










			The Home Depot makes it easy to upgrade your appliances with our free and comprehensive Appliance Delivery service on Appliance Purchases $396 or more. We'll handle everything from uncrating to setup and connection of your new freestanding appliances.Once everything is completed, we'll also remove packing materials and make sure your home is restored to its original condition so you can get back to enjoying your new upgraded appliances. The Home Depot is your ideal source for easy, worry-free appliance upgrades.
		
	































